THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 284 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Nevada State Service Corps is hereby established as a
4 program within the Department of Administration.
5 2. The Department shall:
6 (a) Develop and oversee the Nevada State Service Corps to
7 provide for the placement and mentoring of recent graduates of
8 the Nevada System of Higher Education for temporary service in
9 positions with the Executive Department of the State Government;
10 and
11 (b) Consult with the Nevada System of Higher Education to
12 develop and oversee the Nevada State Service Corps pursuant to
13 paragraph (a).
14 3. In overseeing the Nevada State Service Corps, the
15 Department shall:
16 (a) Recruit students who are graduating or graduated within
17 the immediately preceding year from the Nevada System of Higher
18 Education to participate in the Nevada State Service Corps;
19 (b) Designate positions with the Executive Department of the
20 State Government in which participants may provide temporary
21 service;
22 (c) Match participants with the designated positions and place
23 participants in these positions;
24 (d) Provide mentoring to the participants; and
25 (e) Promote the opportunities to the participants for full-time
26 employment with the Executive Department of the State
27 Government.
28 4. The Director of the Department shall determine the
29 number of students who may participate in the Nevada State
30 Service Corps in each year.
31 5. The Board of Regents of the University of Nevada may
32 request that the Legislative Commission appoint a legislator to
33 serve as an advisor to participants in the Nevada State Service
34 Corps, promote the benefits of state service and provide
35 encouragement to the participants. A legislator appointed
36 pursuant to this subsection serves without compensation and is not
