1 entitled to the per diem and travel expenses provided for state
2 officers and employees generally.
3 6. The Director of the Department may:
4 (a) Apply for and receive gifts, grants, donations and bequests
5 to carry out the provisions of this section; and
6 (b) Adopt regulations to carry out the provisions of this
7 section.
8 Sec. 2. NRS 284.305 is hereby amended to read as follows:
9 284.305 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2,
10 positions in the classified service may be filled by an appointing
11 authority without competitive evaluation only as provided in NRS
12 284.155, 284.300, 284.307, 284.308, 284.309, 284.310, 284.315,
13 284.320, 284.325, 284.327, 284.330, 284.375 and 284.3775 [.] and
14 section 1 of this act.
15 2. The Commission may adopt regulations which provide for
16 filling positions in the classified service without competitive
17 evaluation in cases involving:
18 (a) The appointment of a current employee with a disability to a
19 position at or below the grade of his or her position if the employee
20 becomes unable to perform the essential functions of his or her
21 position with or without reasonable accommodation;
22 (b) The demotion of a current employee;
23 (c) The reemployment of a current or former employee who was
24 or will be adversely affected by layoff, military service,
25 reclassification or a permanent partial disability arising out of and in
26 the course of the employment of the current or former employee; or
27 (d) The reappointment of a current employee.
28 Sec. 3. NRS 284.325 is hereby amended to read as follows:
29 284.325 1. The Commission shall adopt regulations not
30 inconsistent with this section for the certification of qualified
31 persons for temporary service.
32 2. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 3, temporary
33 positions which occur, terminate or recur periodically must be filled
34 by certification in accordance with the regulations adopted by the
35 Commission.
36 3. An agency may appoint persons temporarily for less than
37 160 cumulative hours during any calendar year without regard to the
38 regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant to subsection 1.
39 4. The limitation on hours set forth in subsection 3 does not
40 apply to temporary or part-time service by:
41 (a) A pupil attending the pupil’s last 2 years of high school;
42 (b) A student employed by the college or university the student
43 attends;
44 (c) A person certified for temporary service in accordance with
45 NRS 284.327;
