1 (d) An employee of an events center, museum or research center
2 of the Nevada System of Higher Education;
3 (e) A person employed by the Nevada System of Higher
4 Education in a temporary position which recurs periodically for the
5 registration of students; [or]
6 (f) A person employed by the Nevada System of Higher
7 Education to provide such assistance to a student with a disability or
8 to a student with an identified academic disadvantage as it
9 determines is necessary for the academic success of the student,
10 including, without limitation, a person employed as a tutor, note
11 taker, reader, sign interpreter or test proctor [.] ; or
12 (g) A person employed for temporary service with the Nevada
13 State Service Corps established pursuant to section 1 of this act.
14 5. The acceptance or refusal by an eligible person of a
15 temporary appointment does not affect the person’s standing on the
16 register for permanent employment, nor may the period of
17 temporary service be counted as part of the probationary period in
18 case of subsequent appointment to a permanent position.
19 6. Successive temporary appointments to the same position
20 must not be made under this section.
21 7. As used in this section, “student with an identified academic
22 disadvantage” includes, without limitation, a student who the
23 Nevada System of Higher Education has determined requires the
24 services of a tutor for success in a course of study.
25 Sec. 4. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
